post_text:
Group A students will attend live, in-person classes (on campus) on Mondays.

Group B students will attend live, in-person classes (on campus) on Tuesdays.

On Wednesdays, ALL STUDENTS in Groups A & B will engage in remote learning at home. Teachers and staff will utilize Wednesdays for such activities as remote instruction, lesson planning, professional development and building meetings.

Group A students will resume live, in-person classes (on campus) for Thursdays.

Group B students will attend live (in-person) classes on campus on Fridays.

*Group assignments will be released by next Friday*

Online trainings around such topics as Google Classroom, Google Meet, e-texts, Study Island, Exact Path, the Aspen portal, and Zoom will be offered to families in the upcoming weeks. A website is currently being created to house additional information and resources for parents & guardians.

post_text:
Dear Parents and Guardians,
I just wanted to touch base regarding a very unfortunate and FALSE news story that was created and posted to a local Facebook group page. The story was generated through the use of a realistic app called Break Your Own News. In the false story, someone claimed that there were two cases of Covid-19 identified in the Holbrook Public Schools. The initial post has since been taken down as it contained completely fabricated information. To be clear, there are no cases of COVID-19 in our schools. I thank you in advance for your patience and support as any attempts to make light of such a nationally and globally concerning issue is upsetting to everyone.
Sincerely,
Julie S. Hamilton

I thank you in advance for your patience and support as any attempts to make light of such a nationally and globally concerning issue is upsetting to everyone.

This was the video that was created during our summer administrative leadership retreat and shared with faculty and staff on the opening day of school. Our hope was to showcase our amazing kids and their hopes, dreams, thoughts and expectations for a new school year. Our greatest resource in the classroom isnâ€™t a textbook, a Chromebook or a program...itâ€™s our teachers and staff, so wanted to validate how important they are to the success and fulfillment of our studentâ€™s dreams. Throughout the video, students across grade levels share their personal messages with our learning community. Due to the emotional and positive response the video received, we obtained permission (from the families of participants) to share this video publicly. I hope you enjoy itâ€¦letâ€™s have a great year! Julie Hamilton ğŸ™‚

Thank you to Zack Gorman & H-CAM Studios for their help in making this video a reality!

post_text:
Dear Parents and Guardians,
After re-assessing the water issue with the Holbrook Director of Public Works, it appears that the boiled water ban will NOT be lifted by tomorrow. As the safety of students and staff is our first concern, we will have to cancel our drama program, summer school program and special education in-house programming for tomorrow Friday, July 12. The Champions Program will also be closed until the boiled water ban is lifted. We appreciate the hard work of the Holbrook Department of Public Works as they are making every effort to fix the water issues. We anticipate opening for all of our programs and activities by Monday.
Thank you for your patience. Stay safe!
Sincerely,
Julie Hamilton
Superintendent of Schools

post_text:
Dear Parents and Guardians,
As the situation in town with water pressure and the need to boil water presents a concern for the safety of our students on campus, we will have to cancel our drama, summer school and special education in-house programming for tomorrow Thursday July, 11th. As tomorrow is a field trip day, the Champions program WILL remain open. We recognize that the Holbrook Department of Public Works is making every effort to remedy the problems and anticipate that we will be able to resume full programming on Friday. Thank you for your patience. Stay safe!
Sincerely,
Julie Hamilton

post_text:
Dear HPS Parents & Guardians,
We are so thrilled to be able to finally share with all of you the X2 Aspen Family Portal. Aspen is a secure, web-based student management system created by X2 Development Corporation for school districts to manage all facets of student data from attendance to conduct, grades to schedules, health to special education. While we have used Aspen in-district for many years, this new module will allow parents and guardians to log into Aspen via the Family Portal to view information about their child(ren). We will be fully implementing the Family Portal in the fall of 2019, but would like to have the summer to give parents and guardians time to set up accounts and troubleshoot any issues with logging into the website. Many have already received welcome emails and are in the process of setting up family accounts. If you have not received your welcome email by June 1st, please contact our technology department at jgonzalez@holbrook.k12.ma.us.
Sincerely,
Julie S. Hamilton
Superintendent of Schools
